
[1]lacmus

   LAC'MUS, n. A blue pigment, formed from archil, a species of lichen.
   [See Archil.] It is prepared by bruising the archil, and adding quick
   lime and putrefied urine, or spirit of urine distilled from lime. The
   mixture, after cooling and the evaporation of the fluid, becomes a mass
   of the consistence of paste, which is laid on a board to dry in square
   lumps.
